class_description:
Thrown to indicate that a program has attempted to access an element of
 an annotation whose type has changed after the annotation was compiled
 (or serialized).
 This exception can be thrown by the API used to read annotations
 reflectively.

params.param_description: the Method object for the annotation element

the (erroneous) type of data found in the annotation.
        This string may, but is not required to, contain the value
        as well.  The exact format of the string is unspecified.

Methods.method_description:
Constructs an AnnotationTypeMismatchException for the specified
 annotation type element and found data type.

return_description: the Method object for the incorrectly typed element

Methods.method_description: Returns the Method object for the incorrectly typed element.

return_description: the type of data found in the incorrectly typed element

Methods.method_description:
Returns the type of data found in the incorrectly typed element.
 The returned string may, but is not required to, contain the value
 as well.  The exact format of the string is unspecified.
